The Busia government has employed 120 village administrators, completing its administrative hierarchy that started with the employment of seven subcounty administrators and 35 ward administrators. The village administrators flocked to the County Public Service Board offices to collect their appointment letters on Friday.  Board director of Administration Martin Sikolia said those under 50 years have been employed on a permanent and pensionable basis as per the law. Sikolia said village administrators will coordinate the participation of the village unit in governance, develop capacity and coordinate delivery of services. Â 